CONFSERVER-56081:
h2. Scenario
 # Install Confluence Server or DC with commercial license
 # Go to General Configuration -> License Details

*Expected*: you see a message about commercial license expiration (screenshot below)

!image-2018-07-11-16-27-43-321.png|width=504,height=229!

*Actual*: the message is telling you about evaluation license (screenshot below)

 

!image-2018-07-11-16-27-39-288.png|width=502,height=218!
h2. Root cause

**We have a method ViewOrUpdateLicenseAction#isEvaluationLicense that treats every license as an evaluation one. 
{code:java}
    public boolean isEvaluationLicense() {
        return getConfluenceLicense() != null && getConfluenceLicense().getExpiryDate() != null;
    }

{code}
We should fix it like that:
{code:java}
    public boolean isEvaluationLicense() {
        return Optional.ofNullable(getConfluenceLicense())
                .map(ConfluenceLicense::isEvaluation)
                .orElse(false);
    }
{code}

